---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1} into strips. Crush @blue corn
tortilla chips{1.5%oz} in their bag.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan (for 4
servings, use a large, high-sided pan) over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz}
and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add bell pepper, @Mexican spice blend{1%tbsp}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Stir to
combine. Cook, stirring occasionally, until bell pepper begins to soften and
beef is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1} until combined. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
bell pepper is tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste and season with
@salt{some} and @pepper{some} if desired.

Meanwhile, gently massage @microwavable grain blend{1} in package to break up
grains. Partially open package; microwave for ~{90%seconds}.

> Microwave times may vary—be careful when handling and opening package.

Divide grain blend between #bowls{}. Top with Tex-Mex beef. Garnish with
@sour cream{3%tbsp}, tortilla chips, and @guacamole{4%tbsp}. Serve with
@hot sauce{1%tsp} on the side.

> Ground beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.